  "commit_subject": "[eval] SuperResolution medicine_package \u2014 tested at d056362",
  "commit_body": "9/9 image x scale combinations (3 photos x scales 2/3/4) improved over\nbilinear PSNR using the pretrained FSRCNN (x2/x3/x4) and ESPCN (x3)\ncheckpoints from #27. Best per-card margin over bilinear ranged from\n~2 dB (x4) to ~4 dB (x2).\n\nAlso surfaces a finding worth following up: hybrid mode (SR output +\nenhance()) scored 7-14 dB lower than the SR model alone on every card\n-- enhance()'s fixed sharpening strength, tuned for the blurry\nbilinear-only fallback path, over-sharpens an already-sharp SR\nreconstruction. Documented in docs/algorithm_readme.md \u00a76.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
